# {{ project_name }} — agent guide

This project was generated from [OpenProductKit](https://github.com/ravipurohit1991/OpenProductKit), a product-template with a hexagonal architecture. It is a **monorepo**: a pure-Python core plus thin web / CLI / desktop adapters, with plugins, licensing, migrations and a generated typed client already wired.

Your most likely job here: **replace the bundled "Resource Vault" demo domain (projects / notes / tags) with the owner's real product.** The recipe is below.

## The one rule

**Business logic never leaves `packages/core`.** FastAPI, Typer, React and the desktop shell are delivery mechanisms. If you are writing an `if` that encodes a product decision inside a route, a CLI command or a React component, stop and move it into a core service. The core imports nothing but the standard library.

## Layout

| Path | What it is | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `packages/core` | Domain dataclasses, `ports/` (Protocols), `services/` (use-cases) | Pure Python, zero third-party deps |
| `packages/plugin-api` | Plugin SDK + entry-point registry | Framework — rarely touched |
| `packages/licensing` | Ed25519 offline license tokens, providers | Framework — rarely touched |
| `apps/backend` | FastAPI adapter; owns SQLModel persistence + Alembic migrations | Implements the core's ports |
| `apps/cli` | `{{ cli_name }}` Typer CLI: domain commands **and** the task runner / control plane | |
| `apps/frontend` | React + Vite; talks to the backend through a **generated** typed client | Never hand-write API types |
{%- if desktop_framework == 'pywebview' %}
| `apps/desktop` | pywebview shell; dispatches API calls **in-process** (no HTTP server) | Domain-agnostic — new routes just work |
{%- elif desktop_framework == 'electron' %}
| `apps/desktop-electron` | Electron shell; spawns the backend as a localhost sidecar serving API + UI | Domain-agnostic — new routes just work |
{%- elif desktop_framework == 'tauri' %}
| `apps/desktop-tauri` | Tauri (Rust) shell; spawns the backend as a localhost sidecar serving API + UI | Domain-agnostic — new routes just work |
{%- endif %}
| `extensions/` | Example plugins (basic route, CLI command, license-gated, on-demand marketplace demo) | Removable examples |
| `marketplace/` | `catalog.json` — extensions offered in the Marketplace tab | Vendor-editable |

